Employee Dir
=================

This is directory for API Project. 

* The APIs are defined on server.js
* Default Database configuration available on config.js
* schema File contain MySQL SQL Schema.

Installation Process
--------------------
* Copy this directory into any location
* Go to Current Directory and execute the command 
  npm install (if nodemon not install, install it)
* Start service using 
  nodemon server.js (if nodemon not install, install it)
* this REST server on default port 3001. If started without error available on http://localhost:30001 link

* Get  Skill API - GET METHOD http://localhost:30001/skills
* Get  Specific Skill API - GET METHOD http://localhost:30001/skills/{skill_id}
* Create New SKill - POST METHOD http://localhost:30001/skills
   json - { "name": "skill_name"}
* Delete  Specific Skill API - DELETE METHOD http://localhost:30001/skills/{skill_id}
* Update existing SKill - POST METHOD http://localhost:30001/skills
   json - { "name": "skill_name", "skill_id":"existing skill_id"}


* Get Employee  API - GET METHOD http://localhost:30001/employees
* Get Employee Specific  API - GET METHOD http://localhost:30001/employees/{emp_id}
* Create New  - POST METHOD http://localhost:30001/employees
   json - { "name": "emp_name", "salary":"salary amount","dob": "Date of birt format yyy-mm-dd"}
* Delete Employee Specific  API - DELETE METHOD http://localhost:30001/employees/{emp_id}
* Update existing  - POST METHOD http://localhost:30001/employees
   json - {  "name": "emp_name", "salary":"salary amount","dob": "Date of birt format yyy-mm-dd", "emp_id":"existing emp_id"}


* Get Employee  SKILLS - GET METHOD http://localhost:30001/employee_skills/{emp_id}
* Create new Employee  SKILLS - POST METHOD http://localhost:30001/employee_skills
 json - { "emp_id": "emp id","skill_id":"skill id"}
* Delete Employee specefic SKILLS - DELETE METHOD http://localhost:30001/employee_skills?emp_id= {employee id}&skill_id={skill id}
 json - { "emp_id": "emp id","skill_id":"skill id"}


Employee-details Dir
=================

This is directory for UI Project. 

* Copy this directory into any location
* Go to Current Directory and execute the command 
  npm install (if nodemon not install, install it)
* Start service using 
  npm start
* this REST server on default port 3000. If started without error available on http://localhost:30000 link



Note:

I have attached source code only not with nodemodules.





